        "id": 2917998,
        "name": null,
        "username": "dvansteenderen",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/e9a140/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2020-06-20T20:56:56.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I know there is much love for Valentini on this forum and I understand why (full disclosure: I buy and sell these in the Netherlands!)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=3663082&amp;iNote=8464238\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2019 Azienda Agricola Valentini Cerasuolo d\u2019Abruzzo</strong></a> <em>- Italy, Abruzzi, Cerasuolo d\u2019Abruzzo (10-6-2020)</em><br>\nJust having received 120 bottles of this, anxious to try the 2019 which I did not yet have had the chance to taste.<br>\nToday learned that my pregnant fianc\u00e9 will give birth to a baby boy, so as a celebratory bottle a ros\u00e9 because I do not own any blue wine <img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/images/emoji/unicode/slight_smile.png?v=12\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\">\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This is very good, super pure raspberry fruit. The finish is long and the wine just seem to have a Valentini signature \u201csauce\u201d! <em><strong>(92 pts.)</strong></em></p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/original/3X/8/1/811859ed7583cf5c9a4c90d68f6bed90a20f54b9.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/811859ed7583cf5c9a4c90d68f6bed90a20f54b9\" title=\"\"><img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/8/1/811859ed7583cf5c9a4c90d68f6bed90a20f54b9_2_666x500.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-base62-sha1=\"iq1LuKsvM6xGJ2h7qHACOnimidX\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"666\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/8/1/811859ed7583cf5c9a4c90d68f6bed90a20f54b9_2_666x500.jpeg, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/8/1/811859ed7583cf5c9a4c90d68f6bed90a20f54b9_2_999x750.jpeg 1.5x, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/original/3X/8/1/811859ed7583cf5c9a4c90d68f6bed90a20f54b9.jpeg 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"A66539\"><div class=\"meta\">\n<svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\"></span><span class=\"informations\">1024\u00d7768 106 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg>\n</div></a></div></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=1052250&amp;iNote=8437493\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2009 Azienda Agricola Valentini Trebbiano d\u2019Abruzzo</strong></a> <em>- Italy, Abruzzi, Trebbiano d\u2019Abruzzo (2-6-2020)</em><br>\nSmall tasting glass @ VINEUM during service.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Tasted in Sensory glass made by Roberto Conterno (of Giacomo Conterno) in collaboration with Schott Zwiesel 1872.</p>\n<p>Oh my, this is one of the older Trebbiano\u2019s by Valentini that I have tasted. Personally have more experience with vintages &gt;2010, but it truly does benefit from extensive bottle age. I am going to bury the 2014\u2019s and 2015\u2019s I still have. This was a great wine on the terrace this afternoon, really having the telltale Valentini Trebbiano nose, weight and overall balance throughout the entire bottle! Textural complexity. <em><strong>(93 pts.)</strong></em></p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/original/3X/0/d/0dfa1e276ad39a1db3ee854d547858c16670921c.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/0dfa1e276ad39a1db3ee854d547858c16670921c\" title=\"\"><img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/0/d/0dfa1e276ad39a1db3ee854d547858c16670921c_2_666x500.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-base62-sha1=\"1ZE55eCLXdHKNqQsmTCp9sHwX12\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"666\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/0/d/0dfa1e276ad39a1db3ee854d547858c16670921c_2_666x500.jpeg, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/0/d/0dfa1e276ad39a1db3ee854d547858c16670921c_2_999x750.jpeg 1.5x, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/original/3X/0/d/0dfa1e276ad39a1db3ee854d547858c16670921c.jpeg 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"767163\"><div class=\"meta\">\n<svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\"></span><span class=\"informations\">1024\u00d7768 91.2 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg>\n</div></a></div></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=2580863&amp;iNote=8464273\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2014 Azienda Agricola Valentini Trebbiano d\u2019Abruzzo</strong></a> <em>- Italy, Abruzzi, Trebbiano d\u2019Abruzzo (27-3-2020)</em><br>\nAt home tasting this 2014 vs the 2015 Azienda Agricola Valentini Trebbiano d\u2019Abruzzo. The 2014 slightly has the edge now, however giving the structure of the 2015 I would not be surprised if it will have the upper hand in the future. Both vintages however taste young still and can age for a long time more! Will try to age both vintages some more for a mini vertical in some years to come.<br>\nThis 2014: nectarines and apples. Broad and \u201cfatty\u201d. <em><strong>(94 pts.)</strong></em>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/original/3X/3/5/3573e47bec53df5f65d85373cf3fa1fe7726d6fd.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/3573e47bec53df5f65d85373cf3fa1fe7726d6fd\" title=\"\"><img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/3/5/3573e47bec53df5f65d85373cf3fa1fe7726d6fd_2_375x500.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-base62-sha1=\"7CRBtIeokR1d2bJWIPvYyWZFhVz\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"375\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/3/5/3573e47bec53df5f65d85373cf3fa1fe7726d6fd_2_375x500.jpeg, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/3/5/3573e47bec53df5f65d85373cf3fa1fe7726d6fd_2_562x750.jpeg 1.5x, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/3/5/3573e47bec53df5f65d85373cf3fa1fe7726d6fd_2_750x1000.jpeg 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"766F5B\"><div class=\"meta\">\n<svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\"></span><span class=\"informations\">768\u00d71024 142 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg>\n</div></a></div></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=3350428&amp;iNote=8464275\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><strong>2015 Azienda Agricola Valentini Trebbiano d\u2019Abruzzo</strong></a> <em>- Italy, Abruzzi, Trebbiano d\u2019Abruzzo (27-3-2020)</em><br>\nAt home tasting this 2014 vs the 2015 Azienda Agricola Valentini Trebbiano d\u2019Abruzzo. The 2014 slightly has the edge now, however giving the structure of the 2015 I would not be surprised if it will have the upper hand in the future. Both vintages however taste young still and can age for a long time more! Will try to age both vintages some more for a mini vertical in some years to come.<br>\nThis 2015: yellow apples and limes. Linear and intense. <em><strong>(93 pts.)</strong></em>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/original/3X/e/d/ed69221de19ad925203899f36abb9f6b54c4056d.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/ed69221de19ad925203899f36abb9f6b54c4056d\" title=\"\"><img src=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/e/d/ed69221de19ad925203899f36abb9f6b54c4056d_2_666x500.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-base62-sha1=\"xSepgn93w2HrF6g0QBvUhs6tFU1\" role=\"presentation\" width=\"666\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/e/d/ed69221de19ad925203899f36abb9f6b54c4056d_2_666x500.jpeg, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/optimized/3X/e/d/ed69221de19ad925203899f36abb9f6b54c4056d_2_999x750.jpeg 1.5x, https://www.wineberserkers.com/uploads/db0731/original/3X/e/d/ed69221de19ad925203899f36abb9f6b54c4056d.jpeg 2x\" data-dominant-color=\"91846F\"><div class=\"meta\">\n<svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\"></span><span class=\"informations\">1024\u00d7768 93 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg>\n</div></a></div></p>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">CellarTracker</a></em></p>",
